modules.description: This module provides operations for handling signals, executing formatted commands, removing files or directories recursively, and locating files within a path. It works with strings for file paths and command arguments, using standard format specifiers for safe string interpolation. Concrete use cases include safely running shell commands, cleaning up temporary files, and searching for executable files in a list of directories.

Stores and exposes version metadata including the version string, commit hash, and commit date. Works with string and option types to represent version information. Useful for logging, diagnostics, and displaying build details in applications.

This module combines utilities for system interaction, version tracking, and file management. It supports executing formatted shell commands, recursively removing files, searching paths for executables, and exposing build metadata like version strings and commit hashes. You can safely interpolate command arguments, clean temporary directories, locate binaries, or log application version details. Specific examples include running shell scripts with dynamic arguments, removing temporary directories after execution, and displaying build information in logs.
